posts.name: Max Morehead
posts.cooked:
These results are hilarious. No team is averaging 16 notes a game, and if you are averaging 13, you are a top 25 team at least.

2056 scored around 13 pieces per game at their first event according to OPR (which isn’t reliable to determine how game pieces were intaked, but is at least a starting point). By the same metric 254 scored 14 per game.

At the Heartland Regional last weekend, the high scoring meta was to pass notes to get the amp filled.

Robots were intaking 2-3 notes and passing them before running back with a 4th note to shoot in during amplification.

posts.name: Lotem
posts.cooked:
At Heartland during elims the high-score match we, 3061,  intaked 17 notes in teleop 4 of those being passed with half-field cycles (this was probably our best match with not a lot of defense played on us). our strategy was better outlined in our alliance partners’ post:

Overture 7421 | Build Blog 2024 | Open Alliance

Strategy, we used a 1 Amp/Speaker, 1 Speaker and 1 defensive bot strategy in which after autonomous the first two notes scored from the whole alliance would be in the amp. The amp bot would score the first note while the speaker bot would pass them the second note from half field. While the amp bot was scoring the second note, the speaker bot would be getting ready to shoot into the speaker and as the note enters the speaker the human player would wait until the note was about to be counted to amplify and take full advantage of the 10 second period. During the 10 second period the amp bot would convert to shooting into the speaker for maximum points. The defensive bot would also serve as a passing bot on occasions. Our goal was to try to only score on a the speaker when amplified.

From what we saw this strategy can work with a lot of coordination and shows that this game has a lot to grow.

posts.name: Paul Regnier
posts.cooked: are you counting auto in that? I know for certain we have gotten at least one 10+ cycle match, and with a 4/5 piece that slots right in to 13/16

posts.name: Max Morehead
posts.cooked:
Correct, that counts auto. It’s one thing to intake 13 rings in one game. It’s another thing to average 13 over the course of a tournament, including games where something breaks or people play defense against you. In order to do the latter, you probably have to regularly have games where you do 16+.

Unfortunately, Heartland Regional doesn’t have playoff video up yet (I’ve been sending feeding strategy videos to our strategy team/drive team), but after watching some qual matches, I think that even teams using feeding strategies in playoffs haven’t averaged 16 over the course of a tournament.

My main point is that if you aren’t intaking 13 notes a match, you shouldn’t feel discouraged. If you average 3 notes in auto and 5 notes in teleop, you’re well within alliance captain range at any event.
